@* The dark-mode switch. It carries no server state and needs no round trip: site.js flips
   data-bs-theme on <html> live and writes the cookie the head script reads next time. Its
   checked state is synced by site.js on load, since the theme is only known there (the head
   script may have chosen it from the operating system, which the server cannot see). *@
<div class="form-check form-switch text-body d-flex align-items-center ms-sm-2 my-1 my-sm-0">
    <input class="form-check-input me-2" type="checkbox" role="switch" id="theme-switch"
           aria-label="@L["Dark mode"]" />
    <label class="form-check-label" for="theme-switch">
        <span class="theme-switch-icon" aria-hidden="true"></span>
        <span class="d-sm-none">@L["Dark mode"]</span>
    </label>
</div>
